-- TMX Group Chooses Deana Djurdjevic to Oversee Equities Trading
-- B y   E r i c   L a m
-- 2013-05-30T18:45:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-30/tmx-group-chooses-deana-djurdjevic-to-oversee-equities-trading.html
TMX Group Ltd. (X) , operator of the
Toronto Stock Exchange, named Deana Djurdjevic senior vice-president of equities trading today.  Djurdjevic joined TMX after the exchange operator acquired
Alpha Trading Systems Inc. She was chief trading and data
officer at Alpha, which operated an alternative trading
platform.  The executive has previously worked at financial
institutions including the Bank of Montreal and  Fidelity
Investments , TMX said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Lam in Toronto at 
 elam87@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lynn Thomasson at 
 lthomasson@bloomberg.net  